Effect of different moisture contents (a), drying Damköhler numbers (b), and devolatilization temperature (c) on process of omitting second heating subzone

The results make it clear that an increase in the moisture content causes the flame velocity and flame temperature to decrease. Other physical characteristics of organic particles also affect the flame structure. Volatilization Damköhler number (Davap)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
