				\begin{document}$$\hbox {Da}_\mathrm{vap}$$\end{document} causes a reduction in the mass fraction of available gaseous fuel and a subsequent decrease in the burning velocity. An increase in the volatilization temperature leads to a decrease in the gaseous fuel mass fraction. In addition, the onset of the volatilization process and the maximum of the diagram move toward the reaction zone.

The present research has shown that an increase in the moisture content or Dadry\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
